                            <comment id="233247" author="simmonsja" created="Mon, 10 Sep 2018 16:22:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;can this be closed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73996" author="di.wang" created="Sat, 21 Dec 2013 23:06:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just create &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4409&quot; title=&quot;insanity test_10 (MDT0/OST/MDT1)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4409&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4409&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for DNE failure. Sure I will submit a patch to disable it for MDSCOUNT &amp;gt; 1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73992" author="pjones" created="Sat, 21 Dec 2013 18:21:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Rather than waiting for a patch to work its way through the system, let&apos;s disable the test at the TEI level&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="73990" author="adilger" created="Sat, 21 Dec 2013 18:10:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see several review-dne tests are timing out in insanity and reporting this bug as the cause. Di or Sarah, could you please confirm and/or file a new bug for the review-dne failures. It is likely that no quick solution will be available, so it makes sense to submit a patch to skip the failing test for MDSCOUNT &amp;gt; 1. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="71921" author="utopiabound" created="Tue, 19 Nov 2013 19:38:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Even with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2059&quot; title=&quot;mgc to backup configuration on osd-based llogs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2059&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2059&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixed, the disabled tests related to osd base llogs don&apos;t seem to be working.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
